TITLE: Chinese EV brand Li Auto sees first-quarter deliveries surge by 66%
SUMMARY: Chinese electric car brand Li Auto delivered more cars in March than Xpeng did in the first quarter, according to company releases.

TITLE: Tesla reports 422,875 deliveries for first quarter of 2023
SUMMARY: Tesla just posted its first-quarter vehicle productionÂ and deliveries report for 2023.

TITLE: Huawei reports biggest profit decline ever as U.S. sanctions, pandemic controls hit Chinese giant
SUMMARY: Huawei has sought to diversify into new areas including cloud computing and automotive after a rough few years in which U.S. sanctions have hit the company.

SUMMARY: EVgo's revenue surged over 283% from a year ago as a new initiative to provide chargers for businesses boomed.

SUMMARY: Planet on Wednesday delivered another record quarter of revenue, nearing the top end of its full-year revenue forecast.

SUMMARY: Lululemon's quarterly results beat Wall Street's expectations, sending shares higher.

SUMMARY: Walgreens' quarterly results topped Wall Street's expectations, even as profit declined from a year earlier.

SUMMARY: The financials are the first detailed look at EV profitability as Ford unveils a new financial reporting structure.

SUMMARY: Chinese tech giant Tencent reported Wednesday better-than-expected quarterly revenue, helped by growth in ads within its growing "video accounts" business.

SUMMARY: Investors have been watching to see if Nike's gross margins improve from its direct-to-consumer channels.

SUMMARY: Oracle reported fiscal third quarter 2023 revenue that missed analyst expecations.

SUMMARY: Gap's fiscal fourth quarter results fell short of Wall Street's expectations.

SUMMARY: Lego sales rose as customers bought bigger, more complicated sets such as those from the Harry Potter and Star Wars lines.

SUMMARY: Nordstrom has struggled with slower sales, more markdowns and pressure from activist investor Ryan Cohen.
